   <i> ♪ All we can from today ♪</i>

165
00:08:58,338 --> 00:09:02,207
  <i> ♪ Once we had to listen now</i>
   <i> you'll hear what we say ♪</i>

166
00:09:02,309 --> 00:09:05,844
  <i> ♪ Everything is always OK! ♪</i>

167
00:09:05,946 --> 00:09:13,451
    <i> ♪ Cause being big is all</i>
   <i> it takes! All it takes! ♪</i>

168
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,929
                I think I ate
                too many snacks...

169
00:09:24,031 --> 00:09:27,199
Uh, this doesn't
look like Appleoosa.

170
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:29,568
    [nasty gravelly voice]
    That's because it isn't!

171
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:32,870
       <i> ♪ [eerie music] ♪</i>

172
00:09:32,972 --> 00:09:34,507
   You all heard that, right?

173
00:09:35,309 --> 00:09:39,345
   Uh... Hello? Do you think
   we got on the wrong train?

174
00:09:39,947 --> 00:09:42,781
   I thought trains just took
   you where you wanted to go.

175
00:09:46,119 --> 00:09:50,155
  Sorry. I don't mean to laugh,

176
00:09:50,357 --> 00:09:53,625
       but you three must
       not travel much.

177
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:56,428
    This is Hayseed Junction.

178
00:09:56,830 --> 00:10:00,732
     The train to Appleoosa
     isn't for a few hours..

179
00:10:01,234 --> 00:10:04,904
                Or, you could
                set off on <i>hoof</i>.

180
00:10:05,506 --> 00:10:09,307
        It's treacherous
         <i>and</i> confusing,

181
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:13,178
         unfit for the
         young or timid..

182
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,181
But you three are
grownups. You'll be fine.

183
00:10:16,283 --> 00:10:18,249
I'll write down
some directions.

184
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:22,287
       Maybe we should
       wait for the train.

185
00:10:22,389 --> 00:10:23,655
       And miss the fair?

186
00:10:23,757 --> 00:10:25,724
       We already ended up
       in the wrong place,

187
00:10:25,826 --> 00:10:27,893
      which is exactly what
      we were warned about!

188
00:10:27,995 --> 00:10:30,128
     And.. what if we can't
     follow the directions?

189
00:10:34,668 --> 00:10:37,836
    Come on! We didn't come
    all this way for nothing.

190
00:10:37,938 --> 00:10:40,805
   Besides, I've been through
    a swamp as a young pony,

191
00:10:40,907 --> 00:10:42,741
 as a grownup, it'll be a snap!

192
00:10:43,443 --> 00:10:45,276
         Grownups <i>always</i>
         know the way!

193
00:10:45,378 --> 00:10:47,846
Because being big
is all it takes!

194
00:10:54,588 --> 00:10:57,288
      Sorry. I've got kind
       of a throat thing.

195
00:11:01,294 --> 00:11:06,865
      <i> ♪ [rhythmic piano] ♪</i>

196
00:11:06,967 --> 00:11:13,805
♪♪

197
00:11:16,944 --> 00:11:18,309
           Ah! [splash]

198
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:27,879
♪♪

199
00:11:36,229 --> 00:11:39,230
   Sweetie Belle, are you
   sure this is the right way?

200
00:11:39,332 --> 00:11:43,001
       <i> ♪ [scary music] ♪</i>

201
00:11:43,103 --> 00:11:43,868
         Sweetie Belle?

202
00:11:45,572 --> 00:11:46,237
                      Scootaloo?

203
00:11:47,674 --> 00:11:48,507
         Don't DO that!

204
00:11:49,676 --> 00:11:50,642
       Apple Bloom: Girls?

205
00:11:55,766 --> 00:11:58,183
      Maybe we should head
      back to the station..

206
00:11:58,385 --> 00:12:01,219
      I'm not sure we can.
       I think we're lost.

207
00:12:02,121 --> 00:12:04,523
            Just like Twilight
            and the others said!

208
00:12:04,825 --> 00:12:08,927
 Well, where were you when I was
 feeding and caring for him?

209
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:13,932
    AHHH! Wild swamp ponies!

210
00:12:15,445 --> 00:12:16,145
      Hmph!

211
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:20,439
  We're not wild swamp ponies,
   we're just grownups!

212
00:12:20,641 --> 00:12:23,074
       And we are
      <i>definitely</i> NOT lost.

213
00:12:24,611 --> 00:12:27,278
       OK. But that swamp
       is pretty confusing

214
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:29,014
       if you're not from
       around here.

215
00:12:29,116 --> 00:12:31,183
  I'm Spur and this is Biscuit.

216
00:12:31,985 --> 00:12:36,154
  I'm Apple Bloom, nice to meet
  you, but.. we're not <i>confused</i>.

217
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,525
     We're just... exploring
     new ways to Appleoosa!

218
00:12:40,127 --> 00:12:42,026
        Hey, that's where
        we're going!

219
00:12:42,128 --> 00:12:43,762
          No. It isn't!

220
00:12:44,564 --> 00:12:45,964
        Uh, which is it?

221
00:12:46,066 --> 00:12:48,266
     Biscuit thinks he can
     just take Bloofy, here,

222
00:12:48,368 --> 00:12:49,434
          to the fair.

223
00:12:50,636 --> 00:12:54,105
  Why not? It's just up the
  road and Bloofy's MY pet too.

224
00:12:54,207 --> 00:12:57,509
    Since when? Bloofy's
    never even seen a CROWD,

225
00:12:57,611 --> 00:13:00,179
     which you'd know if you
     ever took care of him...

226
00:13:00,681 --> 00:13:02,447
     Did you ever think
    meeting all those ponies

227
00:13:02,549 --> 00:13:03,882
     might be good for him?

228
00:13:07,554 --> 00:13:09,421
     He seems OK meeting us.

229
00:13:09,823 --> 00:13:12,691
      See? They're grownups
      and THEY get it.

230
00:13:12,793 --> 00:13:15,560
   Bloofy should totally come
   to the fair with me, right?

231
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:17,996
Y'all don't really
think that, do ya?

232
00:13:18,698 --> 00:13:22,667
    Um. Hold on, us
    grownups need to confer.

233
00:13:24,237 --> 00:13:25,203
    What do you girls think?

234
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:28,173
      If they go to the
     fair, we can tag along!

235
00:13:28,275 --> 00:13:30,375
      And Spur probably
      <i>should</i> share Bloofy.

236
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:33,411
   I mean, that's something a
    grownup would say, right?

237
00:13:34,815 --> 00:13:38,683
   As grownup ponies, we think
   you should SHARE Bloofy

238
00:13:38,885 --> 00:13:41,020
      and let Biscuit take
        him to the fair.

239
00:13:42,022 --> 00:13:44,188
      That is some quality
       grownup advice!

240
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:50,261
 But Bloofy's never been around
   anything that exciting!

241
00:13:50,363 --> 00:13:52,297
        What if something
         goes wrong!?

242
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:54,065
We're headed to
the fair too.

243
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:55,967
Since we're such
great advice givers,

244
00:13:56,069 --> 00:13:57,869
feel free to ask
us for more.

245
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:02,707
♪♪

246
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:15,614
♪♪

247
00:14:18,491 --> 00:14:21,593
   Oh! Ho ho! It's everything
   I thought it'd be!

248
00:14:25,165 --> 00:14:27,732
     Well, my goodness, what
     an interesting critter!

249
00:14:27,834 --> 00:14:30,201
    You should enter him
     in the animal showcase.

250
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:32,638
    You'd be sure to win most
      interesting creature!

251
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:36,875
   Animals showcase? That's
   exactly what we should do!

252
00:14:36,977 --> 00:14:41,079
   That seems like a bad idea.
   What do you grownups think?

253
00:14:45,685 --> 00:14:48,653
       <i> ♪ [upbeat music] ♪</i>

254
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:53,992
♪♪

255
00:14:57,230 --> 00:15:06,098
♪♪

256
00:15:06,206 --> 00:15:09,739
            Whoo hoo!

257
00:15:14,347 --> 00:15:16,748
What happened to being
able to ask your advice!?

258
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:19,284
You ran off the
second we got here!

259
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:23,088
                 Where's Biscuit
                 and Bloofy?

260
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:25,823
        That's why I came
        to find you!

261
00:15:26,993 --> 00:15:33,398
         <i> ♪ [fanfare] ♪</i>

262
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:36,134
    Spur: It's one thing to
    bring Bloofy to the fair,

263
00:15:36,236 --> 00:15:38,803
     but it's another to
    stick him in a showcase!

264
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:40,338
      What's the big deal?

265
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,507
       You're supposed
       to be sharing him.

266
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:45,476
   Yeah, I'm with Biscuit. The
    showcase looks like fun.

267
00:15:45,578 --> 00:15:47,445
       Sorry if I think
      taking care of Bloofy

268
00:15:47,547 --> 00:15:49,547
        is more important
        than having fun.

269
00:15:50,917 --> 00:15:52,383
     Bloofy's just excited!

270
00:15:52,485 --> 00:15:54,253
        He probably just
        wants to get out.

271
00:15:55,255 --> 00:15:58,990
      <i> ♪ [delicate music] ♪</i>

272
00:15:59,092 --> 00:16:03,561
               ♪♪

273
00:16:03,663 --> 00:16:06,464
  Are you sure you're not just
  upset you have to share him?

274
00:16:06,566 --> 00:16:08,099
        What if you took
         a little break?

275
00:16:08,501 --> 00:16:10,401
     You mean, like, <i>leave</i>?

276
00:16:10,503 --> 00:16:13,872
  If sharing him is too hard,
  that might be the best thing.

277
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:16,274
     Take our word for
      it. We are grownups..

278
00:16:20,013 --> 00:16:22,080
     I don't know what
    Spur's so worried about;

279
00:16:22,182 --> 00:16:24,015
       Bloofy and Biscuit
         are having fun.

280
00:16:24,117 --> 00:16:26,517
        Yeah. What could
        go wrong?

281
00:16:26,619 --> 00:16:30,355
♪♪

282
00:16:41,201 --> 00:16:47,939
      <i> ♪ [dramatic music] ♪</i>

283
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:50,308
  Me and my big grownup mouth.

284
00:16:56,116 --> 00:16:59,617
       <i> ♪ [tense music] ♪</i>

285
00:16:59,719 --> 00:17:03,288
♪♪

286
00:17:03,390 --> 00:17:05,256
      Do you think this
    qualifies as getting into

287
00:17:05,358 --> 00:17:08,559
   a dangerous situation with
   no grown pony to help us?

288
00:17:09,796 --> 00:17:13,164
 I think WE'RE the grown ponies
 that need to be helping today!

289
00:17:13,266 --> 00:17:16,901
               ♪♪

290
00:17:17,003 --> 00:17:21,071
    BLOOFY! TREATS, TREATS,
   TREATS! Who wants a treat?

291
00:17:21,173 --> 00:17:28,941
♪♪

292
00:17:31,418 --> 00:17:32,683
What do we do now!?

293
00:17:34,821 --> 00:17:35,820
              RUN!

294
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:38,923
♪♪

295
00:17:40,327 --> 00:17:42,761
    I hope you're right about
    the girls coming here.

296
00:17:42,863 --> 00:17:44,729
  Well, once we read Shadetail
   Evergreen's warning

297
00:17:44,831 --> 00:17:47,231
   that the flower grants
   wishes, it wasn't a stretch

298
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,300
     to think they wished
     themselves to the fair.

299
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:50,801
       It's all they were
       talking about.

300
00:17:52,138 --> 00:17:55,106
   Or maybe since we told them
  they were too young to come,

301
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:57,241
    they wished to become
    grownups, then came here

302
00:17:57,343 --> 00:17:58,843
         and caused some
         kind of trouble

303
00:17:58,945 --> 00:18:00,878
        that led to a
        town-wide panic!

304
00:18:04,817 --> 00:18:05,884
    Yeah. Or that.

305
00:18:05,986 --> 00:18:08,553
      Twilight! Fluttershy!
      Oh, thank goodness!

306
00:18:08,655 --> 00:18:10,088
        I know you're not
        gonna believe it,

307
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:11,856
    but it's me, Apple Bloom.

308
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:15,026
   And I'm Scootaloo! We kinda
   got turned into grownups!

309
00:18:15,228 --> 00:18:16,728
     And we thought we could
      take the train here,

310
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:19,163
 since we were old enough, but
 we ended up in the wrong place,

311
00:18:19,265 --> 00:18:20,531
  just like you said we would!

312
00:18:20,633 --> 00:18:21,499
          And got lost.

313
00:18:21,601 --> 00:18:22,734
  Just like you said we would.

314
00:18:22,836 --> 00:18:24,536
     Then we met these foals
     who led us to the fair

315
00:18:24,638 --> 00:18:26,771
    and we tried to give them
   some grownup-style advice,

316
00:18:26,873 --> 00:18:28,272
       but it turned their
       pet into a tornado

317
00:18:28,374 --> 00:18:30,341
       that might destroy
       the whole town!

318
00:18:35,482 --> 00:18:38,516
 Goodness! A Whirling Mungtooth.

319
00:18:38,618 --> 00:18:41,586
  They are very rare, and just
   the cutest little things

320
00:18:41,688 --> 00:18:43,087
    when they're not excited.

321
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,323
       This one's excited.

322
00:18:46,292 --> 00:18:47,892
    Scootaloo: How do we calm him down!?

323
00:18:48,094 --> 00:18:50,695
    When they're young, a
  Mungtooth forms a tight bond

324
00:18:50,797 --> 00:18:52,064
       with its caretaker.

325
00:18:52,165 --> 00:18:55,032
  They're the only ones who can
   get them to stop spinning.

326
00:18:56,603 --> 00:18:58,836
    Spur's the one who really
    took care of Bloofy.

327
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:00,205
      We have to find her!

328
00:19:00,607 --> 00:19:02,106
You all go look
 for Spur.

329
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:03,374
        Fluttershy and I
        will do our best

330
00:19:03,476 --> 00:19:04,809
        to keep everypony
         here safe.

331
00:19:04,911 --> 00:19:15,077
♪♪

332
00:19:15,188 --> 00:19:16,754
         THAT'S Bloofy!?

333
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,858
I'm so sorry, Spur.

334
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,993
     You knew what was best
     for him all along.

335
00:19:22,095 --> 00:19:23,928
       And even though we
       seem like grownups,

336
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,164
     you were way more
      responsible than us.

337
00:19:26,566 --> 00:19:29,367
       What do you mean
      "seem" like grownups?

338
00:19:29,569 --> 00:19:31,536
        Uh, we don't have
        time to explain.

339
00:19:31,638 --> 00:19:33,337
       Right now, we have
        to stop this

340
00:19:33,439 --> 00:19:35,239
       and you're the only
       one who can do it.

341
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:36,341
              How!?

342
00:19:36,843 --> 00:19:39,910
    I'll show you. He mostly
    just needs to see you.

343
00:19:41,815 --> 00:19:47,484
     Hey, there Bloofy-boo.
     It's OK..!

344
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,695
               ♪♪

345
00:19:57,797 --> 00:19:59,730
        How did you know
        what to do?

346
00:19:59,832 --> 00:20:02,467
       After years of
    experience with animals,

347
00:20:02,569 --> 00:20:04,234
                  I've picked up
                   a few things.

348
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,307
        Well, one thing's
         for sure.

349
00:20:09,409 --> 00:20:10,708
    Bloofy definitely earned

350
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:13,077
      the most interesting
      creature prize.

351
00:20:13,179 --> 00:20:15,246
I'm sorry I didn't
listen to you.

352
00:20:15,348 --> 00:20:16,582
           We all are.

353
00:20:17,484 --> 00:20:20,018
     I guess grownups
     aren't always perfect.

354
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:22,253
        They sure aren't.
        But young foals

355
00:20:22,355 --> 00:20:24,822
    pretending to be grownups
     are even less so.

356
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:26,224
        What do you mean?

357
00:20:27,527 --> 00:20:29,360
  There's only one petal left,

358
00:20:29,462 --> 00:20:31,796
    but I think the three of
    you know what to wish for

359
00:20:31,998 --> 00:20:34,465
       and I'm pretty sure
      Starswirl won't mind.

360
00:20:36,703 --> 00:20:38,569
  We wish we were foals again.

361
00:20:48,915 --> 00:20:52,250
       Hold on. You three are
       actually younger than us!?

362
00:20:52,452 --> 00:20:54,252
        The flower turned
        us into grownups,

363
00:20:54,354 --> 00:20:56,587
     so we figured we could
     do whatever we wanted,

364
00:20:56,689 --> 00:20:58,990
       but I guess that's
        not exactly true.

365
00:20:59,092 --> 00:21:01,960
     We did everything real
     grownups told us not to

366
00:21:02,162 --> 00:21:03,961
        and caused all
        kinds of trouble.

367
00:21:04,063 --> 00:21:06,030
      And things could have
        been a lot worse.

368
00:21:06,132 --> 00:21:08,566
         I guess we <i>were</i>
         pretty selfish...

369
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:10,368
       I'm glad you
       learned something.

370
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:12,003
   That's what growing up is,

371
00:21:12,205 --> 00:21:15,006
    which is why you probably
    shouldn't skip any of it.

372
00:21:15,408 --> 00:21:17,708
      I know we didn't make
      the best impression,

373
00:21:17,810 --> 00:21:20,811
  but we sure would like to
  visit you and Bloofy someday.

374
00:21:22,048 --> 00:21:25,416
I guess that'd be
OK, on one condition:

375
00:21:25,518 --> 00:21:28,119
      You get a REAL
      grownup to bring you.

376
00:21:28,521 --> 00:21:29,253
              DEAL!

